HEADWORD: Syriac
<hw>Syr"i*ac</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>Syriacus</ets>, from <ets>Syria</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>syriaque</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or pertaining to Syria, or its
language; <as>as, the <ex>Syriac</ex> version of the
Pentateuch</as>.</def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>The language of
Syria; especially, the ancient language of that
country.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

